{"id":29666877798,"name":"Test","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAG6EihZg","head_branch":"feat/userdetails-soft-refresh-v2","head_sha":"cf053d4b6eefe5152c5133f0d95fa3619e109ce7","path":".github/workflows/run-tests.yml","run_number":54840,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"feat: soft-refresh UserDetails via authz epoch and generation stamps","status":"completed","conclusion":"success","workflow_id":10954,"check_suite_id":80338347650,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAAStInmgg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798","pull_requests":[{"id":4082416672,"number":24493,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/24493","head":{"ref":"feat/userdetails-soft-refresh-v2","sha":"c4332af5c891704368a85160ad0f28d30d1c85c4","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"master","sha":"c3320e59d5bec49c56be7c49b497585e42695325","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-07-19T00:23:56Z","updated_at":"2026-07-19T00:32:31Z","run_started_at":"2026-07-19T00:23:56Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/80338347650","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29666877798/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"feat: soft-refresh UserDetails via authz epoch and generation stamps\n\nReplace role/user-driven mass SessionRegistry.expireNow with a JDBC-backed\ntwo-level invalidation scheme:\n\n- authz_version table (Flyway V2_44_17) holds per-user ('user', \u003cuid\u003e) and\n  per-role ('role', \u003cuid\u003e) generation stamps plus a single global epoch\n  row; every bump advances the epoch in the same transaction as the entity\n  change, so readers can never observe a stamp without its data. The store\n  SQL is PostgreSQL-only like production; H2 test contexts run against an\n  in-memory store wired in H2TestConfig, and feature coverage runs against\n  Postgres.\n- Freshness stamps (checked epoch + effective gen) live on the immutable\n  UserDetailsImpl snapshot itself, so sessions, JWT, and PAT converge on\n  one three-way check in AuthzService.refreshIfStale: epoch fast path,\n  gen re-stamp path, rebuild path. Gen stamps are validated by a second\n  epoch read after the build; if the epoch moved mid-build the gen is\n  stamped 0 (unknown), failing safe.\n- SoftRefreshSecurityContextRepository decorates the HttpSession delegate\n  of the standard security context repository pair: it extracts the\n  session principal, asks refreshIfStale, and persists the re-stamped or\n  rebuilt context. Decorating the repository makes the refresh\n  session-only by construction (JWT, PAT, and stateless authentications\n  never load through it), skips impersonated sessions, and defers the\n  check until a request actually accesses its authentication. No logout,\n  no cookie change.\n- AuthzService memoizes stamped snapshots per username (stamp-before-build\n  invariant) with striped single-flight rebuilds; JWT and PAT share the\n  same cache and gain the gen fast path: bumps for unrelated users\n  re-stamp instead of rebuilding.\n- UserDetailsImpl serialVersionUID is pinned to the pre-stamp shape, so\n  sessions serialized by earlier releases deserialize with stamps 0 and\n  take one soft refresh instead of a forced re-login; no release-boundary\n  session drain is needed (guarded by UserDetailsImplSerializationTest).\n- Role authority/restriction edits and role deletion bump one role key,\n  O(1) regardless of member count. User role/org-unit changes and group\n  membership deltas (import hook owning side + service paths) bump only\n  affected users.\n- Password change, disable, lock, and expiry keep hard session\n  invalidation. PAT account-flag validation builds fresh at token\n  cache-miss since flag changes do not advance the epoch.","author":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"},"id":"cf053d4b6eefe5152c5133f0d95fa3619e109ce7","tree_id":"399d3b1d574b21ecd1fbc81cdc45df89868c3268","timestamp":"2026-07-19T00:23:32Z","committer":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner":{"login":"dhis2","id":1089987,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwODk5ODc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1089987?v=4","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2","gravatar_id":"","type":"Organization","site_admin":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/events{/privacy}","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/following{/other_user}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/followers","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/gists{/gist_id}","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/repos","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/subscriptions"},"name":"dhis2-core","full_name":"dhis2/dhis2-core","description":"DHIS 2 Core. Written in Java. Contains the service layer and Web API.","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core","fork":false,"private":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core","archive_ur